# ─── Entry 20260320-001 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
entry_id: 20260320-001
timestamp: "2026-03-20T10:30:00.000Z"
session_date: 2026-03-20
interaction_type: debugging
phase: deploy
importance: high
status: resolved
objective: Fix PostHog crash + Sentry on web
interaction:
  user_prompt: "following errors ... app is finally rendering"
  assistant_response_summary: |
    PostHog crash: wrong option name. posthog-react-native v4.x uses 'customStorage' not
    'storage' or 'storageProvider'. The SDK silently ignored the wrong field and fell through
    to buildOptimisticAsyncStorage() which throws on web.
    Sentry: @sentry/react-native bundles both SDKs causing malformed URLs. Fixed via
    platform-specific module files (utils/sentry.ts + utils/sentry.web.ts) — Metro's
    .web.ts extension resolution ensures only one SDK is bundled per platform.
    Both fixes committed and deployed via Vercel auto-deploy.
key_decisions:
  - "customStorage is the correct PostHog field name (not storage, not storageProvider)"
  - "Platform-specific modules (.web.ts) are the correct pattern for SDK isolation in Expo"
  - "Web is a primary platform for Cavatrapi — iOS/Android come later"
files_modified:
  - apps/app/app/_layout.tsx
  - apps/app/utils/sentry.ts (new)
  - apps/app/utils/sentry.web.ts (new)
commits:
  - "fix: platform-specific Sentry modules, PostHog localStorage storage on web"
  - "fix: PostHog customStorage (not storage) for web localStorage"

# ─── Entry 20260320-002 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
entry_id: 20260320-002
timestamp: "2026-03-20T11:00:00.000Z"
session_date: 2026-03-20
interaction_type: planning
phase: feature
importance: high
status: planned
objective: VS AI game mode + How to Play screen
interaction:
  user_prompt: "only showing find match no option to play against AI ... we need a how to play section"
  assistant_response_summary: |
    Scanned full app flow. Found: lobby has Find Match (socket) + Local Play (2 humans same
    device) but NO AI opponent mode. @cavatrapi/ai exports chooseBestMove — a pure sync
    function that runs client-side with 500ms budget.
    Planned 5-phase implementation:
    P1: Add @cavatrapi/ai dep + register how-to-play route (modal)
    P2: How to Play screen (6 sections, accessible from home + lobby)
    P3: Lobby VS AI — difficulty pill-row (Easy/Med/Hard) + VS AI button
    P4: AIGameScreen in [gameId].tsx — AI turn via setTimeout(500ms), isThinking badge
    P5: Polish — PostHog events, rematch flow, smoke test
    Key decisions:
    - AI runs client-side (pure function, no socket needed)
    - difficulty pill uses orange accent to distinguish from mode (green) + clock (blue)
    - How to Play as modal-presented screen (router.push + presentation:modal)
    - AI always plays P2, player always P1
    - resign always calls resign('P1') in AI game — player can never resign for AI
key_decisions:
  - "AI runs client-side via @cavatrapi/ai package — no socket needed for AI games"
  - "How to Play is a modal-presented screen, not inline component"
  - "AI difficulty uses orange accent (#fb923c) to distinguish from other pill rows"
  - "chooseBestMove is synchronous — fires in setTimeout(500ms) to keep UI responsive"
pending_implementation: true

